Ticket.

756
01:21:44,572 --> 01:21:46,782
- It says...
- Don't...

757
01:21:47,033 --> 01:21:48,659
It's nothing I need to know.

758
01:21:59,670 --> 01:22:02,006
- Come on, let's see the bell.
Let's see it.

759
01:22:02,173 --> 01:22:04,884
Come on, let's see the bell.
- Show us the bell.

760
01:22:05,092 --> 01:22:07,219
Yeah, let's see the bell.

761
01:22:14,560 --> 01:22:16,228
It's gone.

762
01:22:17,521 --> 01:22:20,316
Where is it?
- I lost it.

763
01:22:20,524 --> 01:22:23,068
I lost the bell from Santa's sleigh.

764
01:22:23,277 --> 01:22:25,070
It's gone?

765
01:22:26,447 --> 01:22:27,740
Don't worry.

766
01:22:27,948 --> 01:22:30,326
- We'll... We'll find it.
Yeah, we'll find it.

767
01:22:30,534 --> 01:22:32,828
Yeah, we'll help you. All of us.

768
01:22:33,037 --> 01:22:35,831
Yeah, let's hurry out
and find it right now.

769
01:22:45,382 --> 01:22:47,092
It's too late.

770
01:22:48,635 --> 01:22:51,096
Gee, that's really too bad.

771
01:22:52,139 --> 01:22:53,766
Really.

772
01:23:08,322 --> 01:23:10,115
I'm sorry.

773
01:23:41,021 --> 01:23:44,983
<i>11344 Edbrooke.</i>

774
01:23:45,191 --> 01:23:50,614
Next stop, 11344 Edbrooke.

775
01:23:57,954 --> 01:23:59,831
Hey, where you going?

776
01:24:00,874 --> 01:24:01,958
Home.

777
01:24:02,125 --> 01:24:05,712
Oh, okay. Merry Christmas.

778
01:24:10,800 --> 01:24:13,678
Thanks for stopping the train for me.

779
01:24:19,559 --> 01:24:21,144
Have a wonderful Christmas.

780
01:24:23,229 --> 01:24:25,732
Watch your step, please.

781
01:24:27,400 --> 01:24:29,360
And merry Christmas.

782
01:24:46,377 --> 01:24:47,670
Look.

783
01:24:50,339 --> 01:24:53,217
Santa got to Billy's house already.

784
01:24:56,012 --> 01:24:58,764
Look, look! Santa got here!

785
01:24:58,931 --> 01:25:00,516
Isn't that amazing?

786
01:25:00,683 --> 01:25:02,101
It is amazing.

787
01:25:09,525 --> 01:25:11,610
It is amazing.

788
01:25:57,990 --> 01:26:00,242
I'm sorry about the bell.

789
01:26:00,868 --> 01:26:03,495
It was a really special present.

790
01:26:03,662 --> 01:26:05,414
Well, you know what they say.

791
01:26:05,581 --> 01:26:07,875
It's the thought that counts.

792
01:26:08,584 --> 01:26:10,002
Yeah.

793
01:26:11,169 --> 01:26:14,047
Well, see you.

794
01:26:16,675 --> 01:26:18,176
Well...

795
01:26:18,844 --> 01:26:20,429
...see you.

796
01:26:21,346 --> 01:26:22,806
See you.

797
01:26:36,611 --> 01:26:39,114
Watch your step, please.

798
01:26:40,365 --> 01:26:41,616
Thank you.

799
01:26:41,783 --> 01:26:44,327
No, thank you.

800
01:26:46,121 --> 01:26:47,873
One thing about trains:

801
01:26:48,039 --> 01:26:50,125
It doesn't matter where they're going.

802
01:26:50,292 --> 01:26:54,337
What matters is deciding to get on.

803
01:27:11,312 --> 01:27:12,814
Merry Christmas!

804
01:27:16,526 --> 01:27:17,735
What?

805
01:27:18,903 --> 01:27:23,408
Merry Christmas!

806
01:28:31,976 --> 01:28:36,313
Wake up. Wake up.
Santa's been here. Santa's been here.

807
01:28:36,480 --> 01:28:38,148
Hurry up. Hurry up!

808
01:28:38,315 --> 01:28:41,652
Mom, Dad, wake up. Wake up!

809
01:28:41,819 --> 01:28:44,822
Santa's been here! Santa's been here!

810
01:28:44,989 --> 01:28:48,909
Mom, Dad, look!
He brought us all kinds of stuff!

811
01:28:49,076 --> 01:28:51,620
Look, a train!

812
01:29:08,053 --> 01:29:13,517
This is the most beautiful-est,
most wonderful-est Christmas ever.

813
01:29:13,725 --> 01:29:15,978
Wait. Look.

814
01:29:17,271 --> 01:29:19,147
Here's one more.

815
01:29:20,691 --> 01:29:22,567
Has your name on it.

816
01:29:51,471 --> 01:29:53,974
<i>Found this on the seat of my sleigh.</i>

817
01:29:54,140 --> 01:29:56,810
<i>Better fix that hole in your pocket.</i>

818
01:29:57,018 --> 01:29:58,228
<i>Mr. C.</i>

819
01:30:09,406 --> 01:30:11,533
Oh, what a beautiful bell.
Who's it from?

820
01:30:11,700 --> 01:30:13,743
- Santa.
- Santa?

821
01:30:13,910 --> 01:30:15,537
Really?

822
01:30:16,579 --> 01:30:18,998
- Oh, that's too bad.
What's this?

823
01:30:20,041 --> 01:30:22,502
Broken. Huh?

824
01:30:22,669 --> 01:30:24,838
Sorry about that, sport.

825
01:30:29,384 --> 01:30:32,512
Come on, kids.
We don't wanna be late.

826
01:30:40,603 --> 01:30:44,065
<i>At one time,
most of my friends could hear the bell.</i>

827
01:30:44,273 --> 01:30:48,277
<i>But as years passed,
it fell silent for all of them.</i>

828
01:30:48,444 --> 01:30:53,741
<i>Even Sarah found, one Christmas, that she
could no longer hear its sweet sound.</i>

829
01:30:53,908 --> 01:30:55,576
<i>Though I've grown old...</i>

830
01:30:55,785 --> 01:30:58,121
<i>...the bell still rings for me.</i>

831
01:30:58,287 --> 01:31:02,375
<i>As it does for all who truly believe.</i>


